        "header": "3Selective Synergistic Learning",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.15527/2606.15527v1/x2.png",
                "caption": "Figure 2:Visualization of the attention map𝐀\\mathbf{A}and object map𝐃\\mathbf{D}.Compared to SlotContrast[slotcontrast], SRL[srl]reduces noise and produces sharper slot assignments.\nHowever, dense alignment also propagates both noise and blur across the two branches.\nConsequently, noisy and spatially blurry representations are still observed in both maps, indicating incomplete resolution of encoder–decoder discrepancy.",
